The Kenya Revenue Authority (KRA) has started waiving penalties for people who defaulted paying taxes over the past five years, as it seeks to net more revenues to fill a gap deepened by the Covid-19 pandemic.
The agency on Monday announced that taxpayers will now get full or partial relief on penalties and interest on the undisclosed taxes, in a programme that runs from January 1 to December 31, 2023.



