“A taxpayer will not be eligible to apply for relief under the programme if he/she is a party to an ongoing litigation in respect to the tax liability or any matter relating to the tax liability,” KRA said.
Those who disclose and pay the taxes will also be issued with a VTDP certificate to prove they took advantage of the programme, the authority stated.
The move comes as KRA struggles to expand its tax base despite an underperforming economy.
In December 2020, it said it had missed revenue collection targets by Sh186.3 billion between March and November as the economy reeled from the impact of the pandemic.
